evals/results/*.json
!evals/results/.gitkeep
# badge.json + latest.json are tracked so the launch artifacts are deterministic:
# the README's shields.io endpoint badge reads badge.json from the raw GitHub URL,
# and the deployed /evals page bakes latest.json at build time (no need to re-run
# the eval, which would require Python for the injecagent sidecar, on Vercel).
# Both are regenerated by `pnpm eval`; commit them when the numbers change.
# injecagent.json stays ignored (intermediate sidecar output, not consumed).
!evals/results/badge.json
!evals/results/latest.json

# Python sidecar (InjecAgent eval) — uv-managed virtualenv + caches
.venv/
